SIMPLE: all_fours
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: All fours
<hw>All` fours"</hw> <ety>[formerly, <er>All` four"</er>.]</ety>
<def>All four legs of a quadruped; or the two legs and two arms of a
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To be</b></col>, <col><b>go</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>run</b></col>, <col><b>on all fours</b></col></mcol> (Fig.),
<cd>to be on the same footing; to correspond (<xex>with</xex>) exactly;
to be alike in all the circumstances to be considered.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧This
example <xex>is on all fours</xex> with the other.⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧No
simile can <xex>go on all fours</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Macaulay.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>All hail</ent>⟦br⟧
